  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "The named structural moment in which liberalism's constitutive contradictions become experientially insoluble for its subjects rather than locally manageable, and the system shifts from promising resolution of those contradictions to promising regulation of the symptoms — losing legitimacy as an ideological system that delivers the resolutions it has historically promised.",
  "name": "Liberalism legitimacy crisis",
